2
1 added subsection (6), until 1 year after that date, and subject to
2 subsection (6), 4 parcels.
3 (ii) Beginning 1 year after the effective date of the
4 amendatory act that added subsection (6), 10 parcels.
5 (b) For each whole 10 acres in excess of the first 10 acres in
6 the parent parcel or parent tract, 1 additional parcel, for up to a
7 maximum of 11 additional parcels.
8 (c) For each whole 40 acres in excess of the first 120 acres
9 in the parent parcel or parent tract, 1 additional parcel.
10 (3) For a parent parcel or parent tract of not less than 20
11 acres, the division may result in a total of 2 parcels in addition
12 to those permitted by subsection (2) if 1 or both of the following
13 apply:
14 (a) Because of the establishment of 1 or more new roads, no
15 new driveway accesses to an existing public road for any of the
16 resulting parcels under subsection (2) or this subsection are
17 created or required.
18 (b) One of the resulting parcels under subsection (2) and this
19 subsection comprises not less than 60% of the area of the parent
20 parcel or parent tract.
21 (4) A parcel of 40 acres or more created by the division of a
22 parent parcel or parent tract shall not be counted toward the
23 number of parcels permitted under subsections (2) and (3) and is
24 not subject to section 109, if the parcel is accessible.
25 (5) A parcel or tract created by an exempt split or a division
26 is not a new parent parcel or parent tract and may be further
27 partitioned or split without being subject to the platting
28 requirements of this act if all of the following requirements are
29 met:
