1 (a) Not less than 10 years have elapsed since the parcel or
2 tract was recorded.
3 (b) The partitioning or splitting results in not more than the
4 following number of parcels, whichever is less:
5 (i) Two parcels for the first 10 acres or fraction thereof in
6 the parcel or tract plus 1 additional parcel for each whole 10
7 acres in excess of the first 10 acres in the parcel or tract.
8 (ii) Seven parcels or 10 parcels if one of the resulting
9 parcels under this subsection comprises not less than 60% of the
10 area of the parcel or tract being partitioned or split.
11 (c) The partitioning or splitting satisfies the requirements
12 of section 109.
13 (6) Beginning on the effective date of the amendatory act that
14 added this subsection, a parcel or tract may be partitioned or
15 split at any time into a greater number of parcels or tracts than
16 otherwise authorized by this section if the partitioning or
17 splitting is authorized by and complies with standards set forth in
18 an ordinance of the municipality or county having authority to
19 approve or disapprove a division under section 109(1).
20 (7) (6) A parcel or tract created under the provisions of
21 subsection (5) or of an ordinance described in subsection (6) may
22 not be further partitioned or split without being subject to the
23 platting requirements of this act, except in accordance with the
24 provisions of subsection (5) or of an ordinance described in
25 subsection (6).
